label.value: Region of Magallanes y de la Antartica Chilena

definition.value: One of Chile's 15 first order administrative divisions. It is the southernmost, largest and second least populated region of Chile. Limita al norte con la XI Region de Aisen del General Carlos Ibanez del Campo, al este con la Republica Argentina y al oeste con el Oceano Pacifico.
One of Chile's 15 first order administrative divisions.

One of Chile's 15 first order administrative divisions. Its capital is the port city of Antofagasta. It comprises three provinces, Antofagasta, El Loa and Tocopilla, It is bordered to the north by Tarapaca and by Atacama to the south.
One of Chile's 15 first order administrative divisions. Its capital is Temuco. The region is divided into two provinces: Malleco in the north and Cautin in the south.
One of Chile's 15 first order administrative divisions. Its capital is Talca.

label.value: Region of the Libertador General Bernardo O'Higgins

definition.value: One of Chile's 15 first order administrative divisions. Its capital is Rancagua. It is subdivided into three provinces. The O'Higgins Region is bordered to the west by the Pacific Ocean, to the east by the Republic of Argentina, to the north by the Valparaiso and Santiago Metropolitan Regions, and to the south by the Maule Region.

A first-order administrative division of Chile. Its capital is Copiapo. It comprises three provinces, Chanaral, Copiapo and Huasco. It is border to the north by Antofagasta and to the south by Coquimbo. It is some 800 km north of the capital Santiago.

One of Chile's 15 first order administrative divisions. It is the country's only landlocked administrative region and contains the nation's capital, Santiago. Limita al norte y al oeste con la V Region de Valparaiso, al sur con la VI Region del Libertador General Bernardo O'Higgins y al este con la Republica Argentina.

One of Chile's 15 first order administrative divisions. Its capital is the port city of Valparaiso. Administratively, Pacific Easter Island (Isla de Pascua), Juan Fernandez Islands and the Desventuradas Islands also fall under the Valparaiso Region's administration.

One of Chile's 15 first order administrative divisions. Its capital is Concepcion. It comprises four provicenes, and is the second most important region of in the country, after the metropolitan area of Santiago. It is bordered to the west by the Pacific Ocean, on the east by Argentina, on the north by Maule Region, and on the south by Araucania Region. Limita al norte con la VII Region del Maule, al sur con la IX Region de la Araucania, al este con la Republica Argentina y al oeste con el Oceano Pacifico.

label.value: Region of Aysen del General Carlos Ibanez del Campo

definition.value: One of Chile's 15 first order administrative divisions. Limita al norte con la X Region de Los Lagos, al sur con la XII Region de Magallanes y de la Antartica Chilena, al este con la Republica Argentina y al oeste con el Oceano Pacifico.

One of Chile's 15 first order administrative divisions. It is some 400 km north of the capital, Santiago. Limita al norte con la III Region de Atacama, al sur con la V Region de Valparaiso, al este con la Republica Argentina y al oeste con el Oceano Pacifico.

One of Chile's 15 first order administrative divisions. It borders the Chilean Arica-Parinacota Region to the north, Bolivia's Oruro department on the east, the Antofagasta Region on the south and the Pacific Ocean on the west.

A populated place. A city in southern Chile administered by the Municipality of Valdivia. It is located at the confluence of the Calle-Calle, Valdivia and Cau-Cau Rivers, approximately 15 km east of the coastal towns of Corral and Niebla.
A populated place.
A census-designated place (CDP) in Apache and Navajo counties in the State of Arizona.
A province of Sri Lanka. The Government of Sri Lanka had temporarily merged it with the Northern Province in 1987 and de-linked it from the North in 2007.
A province of Sri Lanka. Its capital is Anuradhapura.
A province of Sri Lanka. The provincial capital is Badulla. Uva is borderd by Eastern, Southern and Central provinces.
A province of Sri Lanka.
A province of Sri Lanka.
A province of Sri Lanka.
A province of Sri Lanka.
A province of Sri Lanka that consists primarily of mountainous terrain. Both the hill capital Kandy and the city of Nuwara Eliya are located within the Central Province as well as Sri Pada.
A populated place. A town on the south coast of Sri Lanka. It is located in the Southern Province, about 20 km to the North-West of Galle.
A populated place. A town NW of Nuwara Eliya.
A peninsula in the Adriatic Sea. The peninsula is located at the head of the Adriatic between the Gulf of Trieste and the Bay of Kvarner.
A neighborhood of Miami Gardens. Before 2003 it was an independent city.

A province in the west of South Korea. It is bounded to the west by the Yellow Sea, to the north by Gyeonggi-do province, to the south by Jeollabuk-do province, and to the east by Chungcheongbuk-do province.
Not sure why Budapest, Tatabanya.

A province of Kenya, bordering Uganda. One of Kenya's seven administrative provinces outside Nairobi. It is west of the Eastern Rift Valley.

One of eight provinces in Kenya. Its northern boundary is with Ethiopia; the North Eastern Province and Coast Province lie to the east and south; and the remainder of Kenya's provinces, including Central Province, run along its western border. The provincial capital is Embu.
A province of Kenya. It comprises the Indian Ocean coastal strip with the capital city at Mombasa.
A province of Kenya that covers the area around Nyeri to southwest of Mount Kenya.
One of the eight administrative provinces in Kenya. The provincial capital is the town of Garissa, near Coast Province.
One of Kenya's eight administrative provinces; it is in the southwest corner of Kenya. Nyanza includes part of the eastern edge of Lake Victoria.
One of Kenya's eight administrative provinces. It is dominated by the Great Rift Valley.
